*Thanks to those who helped beta test and give ideas!*
**Special thanks to Dan for the night time idea!**
***Thanks to intoxgaming.com and the Brothers of Tragedy (66.55.158.155:27015) server for resources for testing!***


Changes:
Added buy zones (T buyzone is below spawn after floor opens)
Its at night (obviously) but not too dark.
Added gun toss guns with colored trails (available 1:30 after round start)
No door sounds (you could hear them throughout map like you were right next to it)
Changes in Plinko game:
  - Made activation T only (CT's get hurt if they stand on the pads)
  - Switch turns on game after 1:30 into round
  - Added K2 (kill 2 CT's) and K4 (kill 4 CT's) slots.
  - Tweaked space sizes to adjust for K2/4 (death slots larger)
  - Added sign (no, its not the watermelon game or "pachinko"

More changes that you need to figure out by yourself!

Direct .bsp download: http://www.mediafire.com/?zcb0oylobin

- The T's start in a small room with a metal opening floor and 2 vents to escape to another storage room and underground vent to outside.  The CT's can unlock the storage room from the outside when they get there (security door/authorized personel type door) but the T's have ample time to get into vents or prepare for the CT's before they get there.  
- The T's are let out automatically after 30 seconds but there is a button to let them out.  The red inspection wall is breakable (with moderate damage) as to not cause stand offs.  
- There is a sniper tower with 1 scout in it.
- There is a fenced in area and a knife pit with no lips (button inside the pit brings the wall down for steps)
- No buy zones but various guns around the map (scout, M4's, shotgun, grenades, flashes, deagles, and knives)
LR games include:
- Deagle toss on top of the T building onto cross-walk markings (2 heights to choose from)
- Shot for shot (on the back cells by CT building marked with targets)
- Knife/chicken fights (anywhere + the pit)
- Tire race: Push the button between the two lanes by the pit to spawn tires.  On bell sound you push the tire as far as you can.  Who ever makes it farthest standing up or makes it to the end first wins.
- Plinko: A game inspired by [url=http://www.priceisrightinfo.com/PriceIsRightPlinko.JPG]The Price is Right[/url] where the terrorist in LR goes to the top of the game, presses the button to spawn a watermelon, pushes it onto the grate covering the game area, then goes to the bottom and presses the button to open the door and release the watermelon.  The bins at the bottom are labeled with K-D-K-D etc.  If it lands in K, the T gets to KILL the LR CT.  If it lands in D, the T is killed (DIES) by the CT.  I usually just do gun toss or S4S and say I want to play plinko. It works well enough.

Direct .bsp download: http://www.mediafire.com/?zcb0oylobin

This is my first map release and was sort of my learning map for Hammer. I know the lighting is a little cheap, but I took the quick way out. This is a map for the hosties gametype, the CT's start outside in the sun and the T's start in a room underground that they need to climb out of. The map is based inside the hangar and has everything you could ever need for a hosties game with a little something extra. 

Shot for Shot is located in the catwalks above in the hangar.

Arena is located under the Shot for Shot catwalk, their is a ladder to get out of it, just look closely.

One way wall near T spawn.

4 prison cells.

Gun toss is located inside, their is a regular gun toss area and I added my own spin on gun toss as well. Opposite the regular gun toss is bucket gun toss. It is basically like playing basketball and the different buckets mean different things. Green means that the person who tosses loses, they are to be killed upon scoring a green. Blue means that the T can shoot an extra CT (so 2 in total), so go for it for an extra kill! Red, the most difficult one to score, means that the T who scores it, gets to kill all the remaining CT's. Now I know most people won't know or follow these rules, let alone read this paragraph, but I am just trying to makes things more interesting.

Special thanks to ZaLoS, Butterknife and Phraggah for help with texturing, modeling and compiling.

This map sponsored by intox. Gaming, visit us at www.intoxGaming.com

I will keep this in beta for now because I may do something over, but I will probably just go on to the next map, unless their is actual desire for a "new" final.
Enjoy!
